# Frontend and Extension Safety

- Treat all external data as untrusted; validate and escape before rendering.
- Keep extension messaging boundaries explicit (content/background/page bridge).
- Favor progressive enhancement and graceful fallback when APIs fail.
- Keep UI changes accessible (labels, focus order, semantic controls).
- Avoid risky client-side storage of sensitive values.

## Quick pass/fail check

- [ ] Untrusted data is validated/sanitized before use
- [ ] Extension boundary changes are explicit and minimally privileged
- [ ] Accessibility and failure-state behavior are covered
